/**
@class cv::vcucodec::Decoder
@brief VCU Decoder interface for decoding video streams

The VCU Decoder provides hardware-accelerated video decoding on AMD/Xilinx Versal and
Zynq UltraScale+ MPSoC platforms.

Supported codecs:
- AVC/H.264
- HEVC/H.265
- JPEG (VCU2 only)

Use @ref cv::vcucodec::createDecoder "createDecoder" to create an instance, passing the input filename or URL
and a @ref cv::vcucodec::DecoderInitParams "DecoderInitParams" structure to configure codec type, output format, and bit depth.

Supported output FOURCC codes (use @ref cv::vcucodec::Decoder::getFourCCs "Decoder::getFourCCs()" to query at runtime):

| FOURCC | Format | Bit Depth | Chroma | Notes |
|--------|--------|-----------|--------|-------|
| Y800   | Monochrome | 8-bit | 4:0:0 | Grayscale |
| Y010   | Monochrome | 10-bit | 4:0:0 | Grayscale |
| Y012   | Monochrome | 12-bit | 4:0:0 | VCU2 only |
| NV12   | YUV | 8-bit | 4:2:0 | Semi-planar (Y + interleaved UV) |
| I420   | YUV | 8-bit | 4:2:0 | Planar (Y + U + V) (software conversion) |
| P010   | YUV | 10-bit | 4:2:0 | Semi-planar |
| P012   | YUV | 12-bit | 4:2:0 | VCU2 only |
| NV16   | YUV | 8-bit | 4:2:2 | Semi-planar |
| P210   | YUV | 10-bit | 4:2:2 | Semi-planar |
| P212   | YUV | 12-bit | 4:2:2 | VCU2 only |
| I444   | YUV | 8-bit | 4:4:4 | VCU2 only |
| I4AL   | YUV | 10-bit | 4:4:4 | VCU2 only |
| I4CL   | YUV | 12-bit | 4:4:4 | VCU2 only |

Optional software conversion to BGR or BGRA can be enabled via the
@ref cv::vcucodec::DecoderInitParams::fourccConvert "DecoderInitParams::fourccConvert" parameter.

The decoder supports multiple output methods:
- @ref cv::vcucodec::Decoder::nextFrame "nextFrame(frame, frameInfo)" - returns a single-plane copy of the decoded frame
- @ref cv::vcucodec::Decoder::nextFramePlanes "nextFramePlanes(planes, frameInfo)" - returns separate Y and UV planes as copies
- @ref cv::vcucodec::Decoder::nextFramePlanesRef "nextFramePlanesRef(planes, frameInfo, frameToken)" - returns planes by reference with a @ref cv::vcucodec::FrameToken "FrameToken" for lifetime management

The `frame` parameter (OutputArray) receives the decoded frame as a single cv::Mat. For semi-planar
formats like NV12, the UV plane is appended below the Y plane.

The `planes` parameter (OutputArrayOfArrays) receives a vector of cv::Mat, typically planes[0] for Y
and planes[1] for UV (or U and V separately for planar formats).

The @ref cv::vcucodec::RawInfo "RawInfo" structure (frameInfo) contains metadata about the decoded frame including
format, dimensions, stride, crop offsets, and picture structure.

Properties can be queried via @ref cv::vcucodec::Decoder::get "get(propId)" and set via
@ref cv::vcucodec::Decoder::set "set(propId, value)":

| Property | get | set | Description |
|----------|-----|-----|-------------|
| CAP_PROP_FOURCC | ✓ | | Codec type (H264, HEVC, MJPG) |
| CAP_PROP_CODEC_PIXEL_FORMAT | ✓ | | Pixel format of decoded frames (NV12, ...) |
| CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH | ✓ | | Width of decoded frames |
| CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT | ✓ | | Height of decoded frames |
| CAP_PROP_POS_FRAMES | ✓ | | Current frame position in the stream |
| CAP_PROP_FPS | ✓ | | Frame rate from stream (frames per second) |

Additional information methods:
- @ref cv::vcucodec::Decoder::streamInfo "streamInfo()" - returns a multi-line string with stream details:
  resolution, FourCC, profile, level, bit depth, crop offsets (if any), display resolution,
  sequence picture mode, and buffer count/size.
- @ref cv::vcucodec::Decoder::statistics "statistics()" - returns a string with decoding performance:
  total decoding time, frame rate (fps), and number of concealed frames.

See @ref dec_python_examples_anchor "Decoder Python Examples" for usage examples.
*/
